  "announcements": [
    {
      "title": "Lifeguard Health & Well-Being",
      "body": "Hey Team,\n\nAs lifeguards, your primary job is to keep our patrons safe\u2014but you can\u2019t look out for others if you aren\u2019t looking out for yourself first! The heat, sun, and constant alertness can take a heavy toll.\n\nPlease make sure you are practicing good self-care during your shifts:\n\nHydrate Constantly: Don't wait until you're thirsty. Keep a water bottle on your stand and drink throughout the day.\n\nProtect Your Skin: Reapply sunscreen (SPF 30+) every two hours, and utilize your umbrellas, hats, and polarized sunglasses to block UV rays.\n\nStay Sharp on Breaks: Use your rotation breaks to cool down, get into the shade, stretch, and grab a quick, nutritious snack to keep your energy up.\n\nSpeak Up: If you are feeling dizzy, overheated, or excessively fatigued, let a supervisor or a teammate know immediately. We always have your back.\n\nThank you for all your hard work and dedication to keeping our pool safe. Let\u2019s have a great, healthy season!",
      "priority": "info",
      "id": 1781118510989,
      "posted": "2026-06-10 15:08",
